> Well, I can't live with that.
> A strong back 4 is a unit and Luiz is too self-absorbed to be part of any unit.
> Last Sunday, in United's first attack, he made his "trademark" move to slide around his striker and nick the ball as it's played forward. Instead, Van Persie turned him and raced on to fire a shot straight at Cech. No goal, but the opening was made by Luiz's totally unnecessary move. He does this so often. Sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't. When you're a defender those odds aren't good enough.
> And I confess I like defenders who throw themselves to block shots in the box. See Luiz on Rafael's shot for Sunday's offside goal for how not to prevent a shot.
> I could go on, but I won't. As a list, we are completely divided on Luiz, which is fascinating. But if certain Luiz supporters insist on calling him flawless, then I insist on calling him a clown.
